{{Infobox government agency |agency_name = Manitoba Advanced Education and Literacy |type = Department |nativename = |logo = |logo_width = |logo_caption = |seal = |seal_width = |seal_caption = |picture = |picture_width = |picture_caption = |formed = {{Start date|2006|09|21}}<ref name="MLABios"/> |preceding1 = Manitoba Advanced Education and Training |preceding2 = <!-- (etc.) --> |dissolved = {{End date|2016|05|03}}<ref name="WFP2016Cabinet"/> |superseding = |jurisdiction = [[Government of Manitoba]] |headquarters = [[Winnipeg]], [[Manitoba]]<ref name="2010/11 AEL report">{{cite web |title=Annual Report of Manitoba Advanced Education and Literacy (2010-2011) |url=http://www.edu.gov.mb.ca/ar_ael_1011/report.pdf |archiveurl= |archivedate= |format=PDF |accessdate=June 25, 2012 |year=2011 |publisher=Manitoba Advanced Education and Literacy |location=Winnipeg |page= |ref={{harvid|Manitoba AEL|2011}}}}</ref> |coordinates = |employees = 125.75 [[Full-time equivalent|FTE]] (2010-2011)<ref name="2010/11 AEL report p. 52">{{harvnb|Manitoba AEL|2011|p=52}}.</ref> |budget = [[Canadian dollar|CAD$]]620 million (2010-2011)<ref name="2010/11 AEL report p. 52"/> |minister1_name = [[Diane McGifford]] |minister1_pfo = [[Minister of Advanced Education and Literacy (Manitoba)|Minister of Advanced Education and Literacy]]<ref name="MLABios"/> |minister2_name = [[Erin Selby]] |minister2_pfo = [[Minister of Advanced Education and Literacy (Manitoba)|Minister of Advanced Education and Literacy]]<ref name="Minister's bio">{{cite web |url=https://www.gov.mb.ca/minister/minadvedu.html |title=Cabinet Ministers: Erin Selby |publisher=Government of Manitoba|archiveurl= |archivedate= |deadurl= |accessdate=June 25, 2012}}</ref> |minister3_name = [[James Allum]] |minister3_pfo = [[Minister of Advanced Education and Literacy (Manitoba)|Minister of Advanced Education and Literacy]] |minister4_name = [[Peter Bjornson]] |minister4_pfo = Minister of Education and Advanced Learning |minister5_name = [[James Allum]] |minister5_pfo = Minister of Education and Advanced Learning <!-- (etc.) --> |deputyminister1_name = |deputyminister1_pfo = |deputyminister2_name = |deputyminister2_pfo = <!-- (etc.) --> |chief1_name = |chief1_position = |chief2_name = |chief2_position = <!-- (etc.) --> |agency_type = |parent_department = |parent_agency = |child1_agency = |child2_agency = <!-- (etc.) --> |keydocument1= <!-- (etc.) --> |website = {{url|http://www.edu.gov.mb.ca/ael}} |footnotes = |map = |map_width = |map_caption = }} '''Manitoba Advanced Education and Literacy''' was a [[Ministry (government department)|department]] of the [[Government of Manitoba]].<ref name="2010/11 AEL report"/>
In the 2011-2012 Annual Report, the department's stated goal is {{Quote|text=to support high quality adult learning and post-secondary education that meets the needs of all Manitobans. |author=Manitoba Advanced Education and Literacy |source=<ref name="AnnualRpt2011-2012">{{cite web|title=2011-2012 Annual Report|url=http://www.edu.gov.mb.ca/ar_ael_1112/preface.pdf|website=Manitoba Advanced Education and Literacy|publisher=Government of Manitoba|accessdate=18 July 2017}}</ref>}} The listed acts provide the structure under which the department operated <ref name="AnnualRpt2011-2012"/>: *[[The Adult Learning Centres Act]] *[[The Adult Literacy Act]] *[[The Advanced Education Administration Act]] *[[The Brandon University Act ]] *[[The Colleges Act]] *[[The Université de Saint-Boniface Act]] *[[The Council on Post-Secondary Education Act]] *[[The Degree Granting Act]] *[[The Private Vocational Institutions Act]] *[[The Student Aid Act]] *[[The University College of the North Act]] *[[The University of Manitoba Act]] *[[The University of Winnipeg Act]]
[[Diane McGifford]] served as the first minister of the new portfolio from September 21, 2006 to March 28, 2011.<ref name="MLABios"/> [[Erin Selby]] was the [[Minister of Advanced Education and Literacy (Manitoba)|Minister of Advanced Education and Literacy]], from March 28, 2011 - October 18, 2013 .<ref name="MLABios">{{cite web|url=https://www.gov.mb.ca/legislature/members/mla_bio_living.html|title=MLA Biographies - Living|publisher=The Legislative Assembly of Manitoba|accessdate=18 July 2017}}</ref> [[James Allum]] held the position from October 18, 2013 to November 3, 2014.<ref name="MLABios"/>
The Ministry name was changed to Education and Advanced Learning on November 3, 2014 when [[Peter Bjornson]] was appointed.<ref name="MLABios"/> He served until April 29, 2015 when James Allum returned to the office. His term was completed in May 3, 2016.<ref name="MLABios"/>
The Manitoba cabinet was re-organized after the [[Manitoba general election, 2016|provincial general election of 2016]]. The department's responsibilities formed part of the new [[Manitoba Education and Training|Education and Training]] portfolio under the direction of [[Ian Wishart (politician)|Ian Wishart]].<ref name="WFP2016Cabinet">{{cite web|title=A breakdown of provincial cabinet changes|url=http://www.winnipegfreepress.com/local/a-breakdown-of-provincial-cabinet-changes-378042591.html|website=Winnipeg Free Press|accessdate=17 July 2017}}</ref>
